tests: 1-charcopy 2-stringcopy 3-readtest

use install.sh script to test
./install.sh test=0

CHARTEST:
copies single char (2 bytes) to memory at specified offset parameter
to perform char copy test: (copy an 'A' to offset 256
sudo ./install.sh test=0 offset=256 uchar=65
QUICKLY GENERATE TABLE: ./char_offset_test.sh

STRINGTEST:
copies string of length < 1024 byes (Kernel imposed limit) to offset:
sudo ./install.sh test=1 offset=256 string="hello"
QUICKLY GENERATE TABLE: ./string_offset_test.sh

READTEST:
reads specified bytes at offset given (bounds checking is performed)
sudo ./install.sh test=2 rdlen=10 offset=256
QUICKLY GENERATE TABLE: ./read_offset_test.sh
